## Customer Auction History Details [/customers/{nationalId}/auction-history/{historyType}{?page,size,order}]    

Used to get specific auction customer history.

### Get Customer Auction History Details [GET]    

+ Parameters
    + nationalId  (string, required) - customer national Id.
    + historyType  (number, required) - Possible Value for auction history type.
      + Members
            + `won`
            + `lost`
            + `ongoing`
    + page      (number, optional)
      + Default: 0
    + size      (number, optional)
      + Default: 10
    + order     (optional)
      + Default: `asc`
      + Members
            + `asc`
            + `desc`
            
+ Request In case of historyType value equal won (application/json)
 
+ Response 200 (application/json)

    + Attributes 
        + id (number, required)   - id of a product
        + vatRate (number, required)   - rate of VAT percentage
        + msisdn (string , required) -  auction number
        + customerBid (number, required) - the last customer bid.
        + balanceDueBefore (string, required) - the due date to pay balance payment.
        + intent   (enum[string], required)  - return if the customer is won the product by bidding or purchasing.
            + Members
                + `purchase` -  
                + `bid`
        + currentPrice (number, required) - the total auction price.
        + category  - auction category
            + id  (number) - Id of a category.
            + name (string) - name of a category
        + balancePayment (object)
            + status (enum[string]) - one of the below status will be returned 
                + Members
                    + `paid` - it means that the auction number has been alredy paid and there is no farther action .  
                    + `pending` - it means the customer has alredy submit the baank Transfer information and need approval from Finance business there is no farther action .  
                    + `unpaid` - it means the user did not paid the balance payment and it need Action to show to customer to buy the balance amount .  
                    + `expired` - it means the Auction has been experid and the customer did not pay the balance payment and there is no farther action . 
                    + `rejected` - it means the customer has submit the baank Transfer information but he got rejected with reason and it need Action to show to customer to buy the balance amount . 
            + reasonMessage (object) 
                + messageKey (string) - notification message key.
                + parameters (array[string]) - notification message parameters.
        + payments -
            + type (enum[string])  - payment type
                + Members
                    + `deposit` 
                    + `balance` 
            + method (enum[string]) - payment method
                + Members
                    + `creditCard`  
                    + `bankTransfer` 
            + amount (number) - payment amount

        
    + Body
        
            {
              "products": [
                {
